article_title: Iran’s Javad Zarif Heads Home for Consultations on Nuclear Deal
article_text:
VIENNA—Iranian Foreign Minister Javad Zarif headed back to Tehran for what could be critical consultations Sunday evening as a senior U.S. official said all sides now expected nuclear talks between Iran and six major powers to go past the June 30 deadline.

A senior Iranian official confirmed Mr. Zarif was headed to Tehran and would return to the Austrian capital on Tuesday morning. He didn’t say who Mr. Zarif would meet back home,...
